title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1976-10-09
description: Promised Land, Mississippi Half Step, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain, They Love Each Other, Minglewood Blues, Scarlet Begonias, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Sugaree Saint Stephen-> Not Fade Away-> Saint Stephen-> Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Drums-> Samson & Delilah-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Dick's Picks 33 awesome choice for #33  HOTW>Slip>Drums>S&D>Slip>Frank>OMSN is a must!
Dont miss a classic show
amazing this show is awesome, almost perfect sound quality i mean its free what more can you ask for and all that Help on the way and slipknot is insane. this a must for everybody
One of the best This is a show I have been listening too since I first discoved the Dead in the early 80's. This is one of the best shows I have ever heard. A must have!

Good recording, but... ... these tracks are out of phase and fast.  I strongly recommend inverting the left channel and time/pitch stretching the entire show to 103%.  In fact, since I have the time on my hands...
Sweet What a great show, simply awesome
